KW  - Bank runs
KW  - Capital adequacy
KW  - Suspension of convertibility
AB  - In a general equilibrium model with risk neutral and risk averse agents, we show that if banks issue both demand deposits and equity, then free banking is run-proof and efficient. In particular, we obtain the first best insurance solution if there is adequate risk neutral capital. If sufficient risk neutral capital is unavailable, then a partial suspension of convertibility is optimal. In general, therefore, policies like capital adequacy norms and deposit insurance are neither necessary nor desirable.
